WEBVTT

00:07.141 --> 00:09.677
PREVIOUSLY ON
"UNITED STATES OF TARA"...

00:09.710 --> 00:10.778
WHO ARE YOU?

00:10.811 --> 00:12.346
I'M BRYCE CRAINE.

00:12.380 --> 00:14.782
THE RELEVANT TERM HERE
IS "ABUSER ALTER."

00:14.815 --> 00:18.052
IT'S A PERSONALITY MODELED
ON A PRIMARY ABUSER.

00:18.086 --> 00:19.587
HATTARAS ISN'T SEEING TARA
ANYMORE.

00:19.620 --> 00:21.489
BRYCE TRIED TO POISON HIM
WITH CRAB.

00:21.522 --> 00:23.624
THESE ARE TWO DOCTORS
THAT I CAN REFER YOU TO.

00:23.657 --> 00:25.626
ONE OF THEM RESIDES IN CHICAGO,
THE OTHER, BOSTON.

00:25.659 --> 00:28.396
THE ONE IN BOSTON. HIM.

00:28.429 --> 00:30.764
LIONEL TRANE'S DEAD.
IT WAS A CAR ACCIDENT.

00:33.301 --> 00:35.169
Kate: I REALLY LIKE EVAN,
BUT THAT KID...

00:35.203 --> 00:36.270
Evan:
MONTY, COME DOWN HERE!

00:36.304 --> 00:37.638
Max:
THAT KID'S A HANDFUL.

00:37.671 --> 00:39.540
WHY CAN'T WE LIVE
IN THE SAME CITY?

00:39.573 --> 00:41.509
'CAUSE LIFE, MY DEAR,
IS NOT THAT NEAT.

00:41.542 --> 00:43.211
I THINK WE SHOULD SELL THE HOUSE
AND MOVE TO HOUSTON.

00:43.244 --> 00:44.512
ARE YOU SERIOUS?

00:44.545 --> 00:45.813
YOU THINK THAT MOM
NEEDS TO BE LOCKED UP?

00:45.846 --> 00:47.315
ORGANIC VEGGIES?

00:47.348 --> 00:49.617
AND ROUND-THE-CLOCK
PSYCHIATRIC CARE.

00:49.650 --> 00:50.784
IT'S A FANCY NUTHOUSE.

00:53.554 --> 00:55.123
[ As Bryce ]
BOOM!

00:55.156 --> 00:56.490
[ As Tara ]
I'M SORRY.

00:56.524 --> 00:58.192
ORGANIC VEGGIES, HUH?

00:58.226 --> 01:00.161
Max: TENNIS COURTS.

01:00.194 --> 01:02.330
TA-- TARA!

01:04.232 --> 01:05.633
FUCK!

01:12.273 --> 01:14.142
[ As Bryce ]
* WHEN I WAS YOUNG

01:14.175 --> 01:16.310
* IT SEEMED THAT LIFE
WAS SO WONDERFUL *

01:16.344 --> 01:17.811
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

01:20.381 --> 01:22.183
* A MIRACLE

01:22.216 --> 01:23.317
* OH, IT WAS BEAUTIFUL

01:23.351 --> 01:24.752
[ As Tara ]
THIS ENDS TODAY!

01:24.785 --> 01:26.787
* ALL THE BIRDS
IN THE TREES *
AAH!

01:30.758 --> 01:32.893
I DON'T DESERVE THIS!

01:32.926 --> 01:35.363
I DIDN'T DESERVE ANY OF IT!
I HAVE A LIFE TO LEAD!

01:35.396 --> 01:37.598
OH, AND IT'S GOING
SO WELL.

01:37.631 --> 01:39.567
SHALL WE SAY
"SWIMMINGLY"?

01:39.600 --> 01:41.435
[ CHUCKLES ]

01:41.469 --> 01:43.704
YOU HAVE NO IDEA
HOW MUCH CRAZY

01:43.737 --> 01:47.175
IS BOUNCIN' AROUND
THAT LOPSIDED SKULL OF YOURS.

01:47.208 --> 01:49.710
I DESERVE
TO BE LEFT ALONE!

01:49.743 --> 01:52.413
TO BE SET FREE --
FREE TO READ A BOOK

01:52.446 --> 01:55.383
OR JOIN A CLUB
OR MOP THE FUCKING FLOOR!

01:55.416 --> 01:59.220
KILL ME ALREADY, WOULD YA?
ALL YOU DO IS COMPLAIN.

01:59.253 --> 02:01.822
WHATEVER HAPPENED
TO THAT SWEET LITTLE GIRL

02:01.855 --> 02:04.858
WITH THE PUSSY
THAT TASTES JUST LIKE CANDY?

02:04.892 --> 02:06.594
OHH!

02:06.627 --> 02:07.861
AAAAAAH!

02:15.603 --> 02:18.206
DIE!

02:18.239 --> 02:20.341
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

02:22.910 --> 02:23.877
OH.

02:25.879 --> 02:27.215
TARA!

02:27.248 --> 02:28.916
[ SIREN WAILS ]

02:28.949 --> 02:30.418
SWIMMING?

02:30.451 --> 02:31.785
YOU WENT SWIMMING?

02:31.819 --> 02:32.953
YEAH. [ CHUCKLES ]

02:32.986 --> 02:33.954
I LOVE TO SWIM.

02:33.987 --> 02:34.955
I, UH...

02:34.988 --> 02:36.590
IT WAS SO HOT, YOU KNOW?

02:36.624 --> 02:37.891
INDIAN SUMMER AND ALL.
I MEAN, NO OFFENSE TO INDIANS.

02:37.925 --> 02:39.260
I USED TO SWIM COMPETITIVELY.

02:39.293 --> 02:40.261
BUT THE WATER
JUST LOOKED SO COOL...

02:40.294 --> 02:41.629
SHE'S VERY COMPETITIVE.

02:41.662 --> 02:42.630
CHALLENGED ME TO A RACE.

02:42.663 --> 02:43.964
AND REFRESHING.

02:43.997 --> 02:47.235
WELL, IT'S, UH, OBVIOUS
YOU TWO THINK

02:47.268 --> 02:49.237
I'M SOME KIND
OF RETARDED HILLBILLY,

02:49.270 --> 02:51.672
SO, UH, I'M GONNA
GO TYPE YOUR LITTLE STORY

02:51.705 --> 02:54.242
IN OUR BRAND-NEW
"BIG-CITY TRUTH MACHINE"

02:54.275 --> 02:57.945
AND WAIT FOR THE RESULTS WITH
A TIN CUP FULL OF MOONSHINE.

02:57.978 --> 03:01.949
MAYBE I'LL TAKE A SHIT AND CLEAN
MY ASSHOLE WITH A CORNCOB.

03:01.982 --> 03:04.818
Y'ALL STAY PUT NOW,
Y'HEAR?

03:06.520 --> 03:07.521
Holy fucking shit!

03:07.555 --> 03:08.922
Max, hold it together.

03:08.956 --> 03:10.358
If he figures out
what happened back there,

03:10.391 --> 03:11.359
they'll throw me
in state.

03:11.392 --> 03:12.660
Tara --

03:12.693 --> 03:14.495
YOU DO NOT
WANT ME IN STATE.

03:14.528 --> 03:15.996
I'M TALKING
FUCKING "SHUTTER ISLAND."

03:16.029 --> 03:18.399
YOU KNOW, PADDED ROOMS
AND DRUGS AND DROOLING

03:18.432 --> 03:20.501
AND STRAITJACKETS,
THROW AWAY THE KEY.

03:20.534 --> 03:21.669
YOU JUMPED OFF
A GODDAMN BRIDGE!

03:21.702 --> 03:23.804
BECAUSE I'M CRAZY.

03:23.837 --> 03:26.407
BUT YOU CAN'T LET THEM TAKE ME.
I'LL ROT UP THERE.

03:26.440 --> 03:28.576
AND I CAN'T GO
TO THAT FUCKING COUNTRY CLUB

03:28.609 --> 03:29.843
CHARMAINE CAME UP WITH,
EITHER.

03:29.877 --> 03:31.445
YEAH, YEAH,
YOU'RE RIGHT.

03:31.479 --> 03:33.314
LET'S JUST HEAD HOME,
GRAB A BUCKET OF CHICKEN,

03:33.347 --> 03:35.516
TELL THE KIDS YOU AUDITIONED
FOR THE UNIVERSAL STUNT SHOW.

03:35.549 --> 03:37.885
THAT'S NOT WHAT I'M SAYING.
I NEED REAL HELP.

03:37.918 --> 03:39.987
WHAT DOES THAT EVEN
FUCKING MEAN ANYMORE?

03:40.020 --> 03:42.356
[ SIGHS ]

03:42.390 --> 03:43.357
BOSTON.

03:43.391 --> 03:44.358
WHAT?

03:44.392 --> 03:45.526
I NEED TO GO TO BOSTON.

03:45.559 --> 03:47.395
HATTARAS SAID
I SHOULD GO THERE.

03:47.428 --> 03:48.729
THERE'S A DOCTOR THERE
WHO'S SUPPOSED TO BE THE BEST --

03:48.762 --> 03:51.499
WHAT THE FUCK WAS THAT?
HUH?

03:51.532 --> 03:53.801
I WAS TRYING
TO HELP YOU --

03:53.834 --> 03:55.403
ALL OF YOU.

03:56.870 --> 03:58.406
[ SIGHS ]

03:58.439 --> 04:00.574
PLEASE, MAX.

04:02.042 --> 04:03.544
BOSTON.

04:05.913 --> 04:07.981
WE CAN'T TELL ANYBODY
ABOUT THIS.

04:10.418 --> 04:11.952
I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU CAME HOME!

04:11.985 --> 04:14.388
WE TALKED ABOUT THIS!
YOU WERE ON YOUR WAY!

04:14.422 --> 04:15.689
I MEAN,
WHAT THE FUCK?

04:15.723 --> 04:17.891
WE CHANGED OUR MINDS.

04:17.925 --> 04:19.560
BUT BOSTON?

04:19.593 --> 04:20.961
YEAH, IT'S THE BEST
IN THE COUNTRY.

04:20.994 --> 04:22.763
THEY HAVE A THREE MONTH
IN-PATIENT PROGRAM

04:22.796 --> 04:25.466
FOLLOWED BY ONGOING AFTERCARE
AS LONG AS I NEED.

04:25.499 --> 04:28.869
FOR SOMEONE WHO'S ABOUT TO
HOP IN THE FIRST CLOWN CAR
TO GOOFYVILLE, MASS.,

04:28.902 --> 04:30.604
YOU SEEM
A WEE BIT KEYED UP.

04:30.638 --> 04:32.039
YES...KATE.

04:32.072 --> 04:35.443
BECAUSE, KATE,
I AM READY TO FIGHT.

04:35.476 --> 04:37.445
I LOOKED AT
THE WORST PARTS OF MYSELF

04:37.478 --> 04:40.881
RIGHT IN THE EYE AND SAID,
"I MEAN SOMETHING.

04:40.914 --> 04:43.083
I MATTER.
I HAVE A LIFE TO LEAD."

04:43.116 --> 04:46.954
THAT'S GREAT,
BUT WHAT IF BRYCE COMES BACK?

04:46.987 --> 04:49.022
[ CHUCKLES ]

04:50.758 --> 04:52.059
BRYCE IS DEAD.

04:52.092 --> 04:53.060
WHAT?

04:53.093 --> 04:54.495
DON'T. JUST --

04:54.528 --> 04:55.463
DAD, IS THIS
WHAT YOU WANT?

04:56.964 --> 04:58.499
FUCK NO!

04:58.532 --> 05:00.934
WHAT I WANT IS
TO GET THE HELL OUT OF HERE!

05:00.968 --> 05:03.604
I'M DONE WITH IT ALL!

05:03.637 --> 05:05.038
FUCK THE WHOLE
GODDAMN THING!

05:05.072 --> 05:07.040
YES. HELL YES, MARSH.

05:07.074 --> 05:09.510
I-I WANT YOUR MOM
TO GET THE BEST HELP POSSIBLE.

05:09.543 --> 05:11.445
WE STILL HAVE SOME DETAILS
TO FIGURE OUT.

05:11.479 --> 05:12.880
TOP OF THE LIST --
MOOSH.

05:12.913 --> 05:14.615
WE DON'T WANT TO TAKE YOU
OUT OF SCHOOL.

05:14.648 --> 05:15.849
WELL, IF IT'S ONLY GONNA BE
THREE MONTHS,

05:15.883 --> 05:17.050
WHY DON'T I JUST
STAY HERE?

05:17.084 --> 05:18.952
BY YOURSELF?
ABSOLUTELY NOT.

05:18.986 --> 05:19.953
THEN I'LL STAY
WITH GRANDMA SANDY.

05:19.987 --> 05:20.954
ABSOLUTELY NOT!

05:20.988 --> 05:22.456
ABSOLUTELY NOT.

05:22.490 --> 05:24.592
LOOK, I GOT IT UNDER CONTROL,
MARSH, OKAY?

05:24.625 --> 05:26.594
WE'RE GONNA MAKE SURE
YOU'RE TAKEN CARE OF, BUDDY.

05:26.627 --> 05:29.597
AND, UH, I HAVE
ONE MORE FAVOR TO ASK.

05:29.630 --> 05:31.799
OH, YOU'VE GOT SOME
BIG, HAIRY BALLS, BABY.

05:31.832 --> 05:33.434
[ SIGHS ]

05:33.467 --> 05:35.035
IT'S MINOR.
I THINK YOU'LL LIKE IT.

05:36.737 --> 05:38.872
IT WOULD MEAN A LOT
TO ME

05:38.906 --> 05:42.476
IF WE HAD
ONE LAST FAMILY SUPPER

05:42.510 --> 05:44.778
THAT WE ALL MAKE
TOGETHER.

05:44.812 --> 05:46.914
KATE, I HAVEN'T MET EVAN YET.
I'D LIKE YOU TO BRING HIM.

05:46.947 --> 05:49.517
SURE. SHOULD I TELL HIM
BRING MONTY?

05:49.550 --> 05:51.485
NO.
NO.

05:51.519 --> 05:52.753
AND, MARSHALL,
I WAS THINKING

05:52.786 --> 05:54.722
YOU COULD BE
OUR CHEF DE CUISINE

05:54.755 --> 05:56.156
AND I COULD BE
YOUR SOUS CHEF.

05:56.189 --> 05:57.791
YEAH,
THAT'S AN EXCELLENT IDEA,

05:57.825 --> 05:59.493
SEEING THAT
LESS THAN 24 HOURS AGO,

05:59.527 --> 06:00.794
YOU PUNCHED ME
IN THE FACE.

06:00.828 --> 06:02.563
OH, GOD.

06:02.596 --> 06:04.765
LOOK, MARSH...
I KNOW --

06:04.798 --> 06:06.834
NO, A-A DINNER PARTY
SOUNDS DELIGHTFUL.

06:06.867 --> 06:08.869
IT'S EXACTLY
WHAT THIS FAMILY NEEDS.

06:08.902 --> 06:10.003
SEND ME AN INVITATION.

06:18.078 --> 06:19.046
OH.

06:19.079 --> 06:20.414
HEY.

06:21.649 --> 06:23.083
WHEN YOU GET TO BOSTON,

06:23.116 --> 06:25.819
FORGET ALL THAT WORLD-FAMOUS
CLAM CHOWDER STUFF.

06:25.853 --> 06:28.155
THERE IS A McDONALD'S
NEAR FANEUIL HALL --

06:28.188 --> 06:29.857
I'M NOT IN THE MOOD,
BUDDY.

06:29.890 --> 06:31.992
I JUST WANT
TO GET THROUGH THIS WEEK,

06:32.025 --> 06:34.495
GET HER IN THE CAR,
AND GET HER TO THE DOCTOR'S.

06:34.528 --> 06:37.197
I MEAN, THIS THING IS...
SO MUCH MORE COMPLICATED.

06:37.230 --> 06:38.932
IT'S TOTALLY FUCKED.

06:38.966 --> 06:42.169
AND, UH, I'M JUST --
I'M BARELY HANGING ON.

06:42.202 --> 06:45.773
THAT'S WHY
I BROUGHT THIS.

06:45.806 --> 06:48.008
REMEMBER WHEN YOU SAID
WE SHOULD OPEN THIS

06:48.041 --> 06:49.443
WHEN WE REALLY NEED IT?

06:49.477 --> 06:50.478
WELL...

06:50.511 --> 06:51.545
[ CORK POPS ]

06:51.579 --> 06:52.813
WE REALLY NEED IT.

06:52.846 --> 06:54.715
[ CHUCKLES ]

06:54.748 --> 06:55.816
WHOO!

06:55.849 --> 06:58.018
[ Strained ] YEAH. OHH.

06:58.051 --> 06:59.520
WHAT HAPPENED TO US?

06:59.553 --> 07:01.121
BY NOW,
WEREN'T WE SUPPOSED TO OWN

07:01.154 --> 07:04.858
THE WORLD'S FIRST COMBINATION
STRIP CLUB AND PANCAKE HOUSE?

07:04.892 --> 07:05.993
"TITCAKES."

07:06.026 --> 07:07.227
[ LAUGHS ]

07:07.260 --> 07:09.630
I ALMOST FORGOT
ABOUT THAT.

07:12.800 --> 07:15.068
AM I STILL
MARSHALL'S GODFATHER?

07:15.102 --> 07:16.470
NO.

07:16.504 --> 07:18.038
NO,
YOU LOST GODFATHER STATUS

07:18.071 --> 07:20.240
WHEN YOU ATE
THAT PLATE OF HASH BROWNIES

07:20.273 --> 07:23.010
AND STOLE MY JOHN DEERE,
TRIED TO OUTRUN THE COPS.

07:23.043 --> 07:26.113
THE FACT
THAT THEY WERE ON FOOT

07:26.146 --> 07:29.049
SHOULD'VE TOLD ME I WASN'T GOING
AS FAST AS I THOUGHT I WAS.

07:29.082 --> 07:30.684
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

07:30.718 --> 07:33.921
LISTEN, I'VE DONE
A LOT OF GROWING UP.

07:33.954 --> 07:35.656
AND CHARMAINE
WAS TELLING ME

07:35.689 --> 07:38.726
THAT YOU GUYS DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO DO ABOUT MARSHALL,

07:38.759 --> 07:43.664
SO...
WHAT I WAS THINKING WAS...

07:43.697 --> 07:45.866
HE SHOULD MOVE TO HOUSTON
WITH US

07:45.899 --> 07:48.035
AND WE COULD
TAKE CARE OF HIM.

07:48.068 --> 07:49.703
YOU KNOW, AT LEAST
UNTIL YOU GUYS GET BACK.

07:54.241 --> 07:55.543
ARE YOU SERIOUS?

07:55.576 --> 07:57.144
YEAH.

07:59.647 --> 08:00.714
THANK YOU.

08:00.748 --> 08:02.716
[ CLICKS TONGUE ]

08:02.750 --> 08:04.117
HEY.

08:04.151 --> 08:05.686
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

08:05.719 --> 08:07.187
ANY CHANCE I CAN TRICK YOU
INTO MAKING

08:07.220 --> 08:10.257
A BATCH OF YOUR FAMOUS
BLOOD-ORANGE MACAROONS?

08:13.694 --> 08:14.928
[ SIGHS ]

08:14.962 --> 08:16.997
LOOK, I KNOW
YOU'RE HURT, ANGRY,

08:17.030 --> 08:19.266
AND -- AND YOU HAVE
EVERY RIGHT TO BE.

08:19.299 --> 08:21.769
BUT I'M BEGGING YOU --
PLEASE DON'T SHUT ME OUT.

08:21.802 --> 08:23.170
I'M NOT.

08:23.203 --> 08:25.806
NO, YOU ARE,
AND YOU PROBABLY SHOULD,

08:25.839 --> 08:27.841
BUT I'M ASKING YOU
NOT TO,

08:27.875 --> 08:29.943
'CAUSE I'M GOING AWAY
FOR A WHILE.

08:29.977 --> 08:31.612
AND I DON'T WANT YOU
TO FORGET

08:31.645 --> 08:33.681
THAT EVEN THOUGH
WE'VE HAD A TOUGH GO OF IT,

08:33.714 --> 08:35.282
[ Chuckling ]
TO SAY THE LEAST,

08:35.315 --> 08:39.953
I CAN ALSO BE FUN, LOVING,
CHARMING, QUIRKY,

08:39.987 --> 08:42.723
AND FULL OF SURPRISES.

08:46.193 --> 08:48.528
AND I LOVE MY SON.

08:50.030 --> 08:52.600
SORRY. I DIDN'T THINK
YOU WERE GONNA GET THAT WET.

08:54.602 --> 08:56.737
SO...

08:56.770 --> 08:59.707
I AM PUTTING YOU ON NOTICE,
MARSHALL GREGSON.

08:59.740 --> 09:01.208
YOU MAY HATE ME NOW,

09:01.241 --> 09:03.877
BUT I'VE GOT
ABOUT 36 HOURS LEFT,

09:03.911 --> 09:06.113
AND...

09:06.146 --> 09:07.915
I'M GONNA GETCHA.

09:10.784 --> 09:12.953
[ SIGHS ]

09:12.986 --> 09:15.723
Neil: OH, YEAH.

09:15.756 --> 09:17.224
I'M SORRY --
WHY ARE WE DOING THIS?

09:17.257 --> 09:18.792
BECAUSE I'M TRYING TO --

09:18.826 --> 09:20.594
PUT THE PANCAKES
CLOSER TO YOUR BODY.

09:20.628 --> 09:22.195
YES!

09:22.229 --> 09:23.764
OH. OH!

09:23.797 --> 09:25.799
THIS IS WEIRD.
I'M NOT DOING THIS ANYMORE.

09:25.833 --> 09:28.135
YOU GUYS COME UP WITH
THE STUPIDEST SHIT
WHEN YOU GET DRUNK.

09:28.168 --> 09:30.170
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.
UNH-UNH. YOU KNOW WHAT?

09:30.203 --> 09:31.839
NOT EVERYTHING WE DO
IS GOLD,

09:31.872 --> 09:34.341
BUT SOMETIMES
WE HIT THE BULL'S-EYE.

09:34.374 --> 09:39.046
LIKE THIS -- I WANT MARSHALL
TO COME WITH US TO HOUSTON

09:39.079 --> 09:41.181
WHILE MAX
IS IN BOSTON WITH TARA.

09:41.214 --> 09:42.850
WAS THAT YOUR IDEA?

09:42.883 --> 09:45.686
YEAH -- WELL, HE'S A GOOD KID,
YOU KNOW?

09:45.719 --> 09:47.287
AND HE'S CRAZY ABOUT YOU.

09:47.320 --> 09:50.858
AND...I JUST THINK
IT'D BE THE RIGHT THING TO DO.

09:50.891 --> 09:51.859
THAT'S REALLY SWEET.

09:51.892 --> 09:53.761
MM.

09:53.794 --> 09:56.897
BUT...YOU KNOW, IF WE'RE GONNA
BE TAKING CARE OF MARSHALL,

09:56.930 --> 09:59.132
MAYBE IT'D BE BEST FOR HIM
IF WE DIDN'T GO TO HOUSTON

09:59.166 --> 10:00.934
AND WE JUST STAYED HERE.

10:00.968 --> 10:02.736
WHAT? NO.
WE HAV TO GO TO HOUSTON.

10:02.770 --> 10:04.672
I MEAN, I PROMISED THEM
I WAS COMING.

10:04.705 --> 10:05.673
WELL, JUST TELL THEM
YOU CHANGED YOUR MIND.

10:05.706 --> 10:07.107
[ Laughing ] WHY?!

10:07.140 --> 10:08.842
BECAUSE HOUSTON IS
A TERRIBLE PLACE TO LIVE.

10:08.876 --> 10:10.711
WHAT -- SAYS WHO?

10:10.744 --> 10:12.179
ONE OF MY MOMMY FRIENDS KNOWS
SOMEBODY THAT MOVED TO HOUSTON.

10:12.212 --> 10:14.047
A-AND?

10:14.081 --> 10:17.117
AND I DON'T WANT YOU TO END UP
EATING YOUR OWN LEGS.

10:17.150 --> 10:19.286
WHAT THE FUCK
ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

10:19.319 --> 10:20.921
THE MEXICAN DRUG CARTEL.

10:20.954 --> 10:23.123
OH, MY GOD.
YOU'RE OUT OF YOUR FUCKING MIND.

10:23.156 --> 10:24.424
NO!

10:24.457 --> 10:26.093
LOOK -- HEY, HEY,
WE TALKED ABOUT THIS.

10:26.126 --> 10:27.995
A DECISION WAS MADE,
ALL RIGHT?

10:28.028 --> 10:32.700
SO THIS IS A DONE DEAL,
SO STRAP ON YOUR SIX-GUNS

10:32.733 --> 10:34.234
AROUND
THOSE SEXY LITTLE HIPS

10:34.267 --> 10:37.437
'CAUSE YOU ARE GOING
TO HOUSTON, THERE, FILLY.

10:37.470 --> 10:40.273
AND THESE PANCAKES
ARE COMIN' WITH ME,

10:40.307 --> 10:41.942
[ Southern accent ]
YA DARN DESERT FLOWER.

10:41.975 --> 10:42.943
OHH!

10:42.976 --> 10:44.778
Kate: SEE, TECHNICALLY,

10:44.812 --> 10:46.246
YOU'RE NOT HELPING MOM --
YOU'RE HELPING ME,

10:46.279 --> 10:47.781
BECAUSE I CAN'T
TELL THE DIFFERENCE

10:47.815 --> 10:49.783
BETWEEN A BULB OF GARLIC
AND A SHALLOT.

10:49.817 --> 10:51.351
[ GASPS ]
OOH! WHAT'S THIS?

10:51.384 --> 10:52.452
UH, A CAT TURD.

10:52.485 --> 10:54.888
UGH!

10:54.922 --> 10:56.990
SPEAKING OF
DISGUSTING SHIT HEAPS,

10:57.024 --> 11:00.393
WHAT'S THIS I'M HEARING ABOUT
YOU MOVING TO HOUSTON, PARDNER?

11:00.427 --> 11:01.862
YEAH.

11:01.895 --> 11:02.896
WELL, ARE YOU
OKAY WITH THAT?

11:02.930 --> 11:04.264
I DON'T REALLY CARE.

11:04.297 --> 11:07.701
WHAT DIFFERENCE DOES
ANYTHING MAKE AT THIS POINT?

11:07.735 --> 11:09.336
THIS IS IT, MOOSH.
IT'S ALL WE GOT.

11:09.369 --> 11:11.304
IT'S NOTHING TO BE
SAD OR HAPPY ABOUT.

11:11.338 --> 11:14.474
IT'S JUST...
IT IS WHAT IT IS.

11:14.507 --> 11:17.344
YOU KNOW, I WANT TO SHOOT MYSELF
IN THE HEAD

11:17.377 --> 11:21.314
WHEN I THINK ABOUT MOM TRYING
TO WIPE AWAY YEARS AND YEARS

11:21.348 --> 11:24.718
OF PAIN AND DISAPPOINTMENT
WITH A HUG OR A KISS

11:24.752 --> 11:26.453
OR A FUCKING
FAMILY DINNER.

11:26.486 --> 11:30.991
WELL, SHE DOESN'T KNOW
WHAT ELSE TO DO.

11:31.024 --> 11:32.325
HERE'S THE TRUTH, KATE --

11:32.359 --> 11:34.294
I DON'T HAVE ANY ROOM
TO GIVE A SHIT.

11:34.327 --> 11:36.263
I'M FINDING IT HARD
TO CARE ABOUT HER.

11:38.966 --> 11:41.301
YOU KNOW, I WAS DRIVING DOWN
LOWELL AVENUE THE OTHER DAY,

11:41.334 --> 11:46.273
AND -- AND, UH, PEOPLE ARE
BRINGING FLOWERS, MEMENTOS.

11:46.306 --> 11:49.743
IT'S -- IT'S KIND OF...
LIKE A MEMORIAL.

11:49.777 --> 11:51.912
IT'S REALLY BEAUTIFUL.

11:51.945 --> 11:53.947
DO YOU THINK THAT MAYBE
YOU WOULD WANT TO GO OR --

11:53.981 --> 11:56.216
NO.

11:56.249 --> 11:59.219
HEY, KATE, EVAN JUST GOT HERE.
YOU BETTER GET IN HERE.

11:59.252 --> 12:00.353
OH, SHIT. IS HE --
OH,
THEY'RE EATING HIM ALIVE.

12:00.387 --> 12:01.354
OHH!

12:01.388 --> 12:02.355
WHY'D YOU GET DIVORCED?

12:02.389 --> 12:03.356
DID YOU LEAVE HER?

12:03.390 --> 12:04.424
WERE YOU JUST TOO YOUNG?

12:04.457 --> 12:05.859
OR DID SHE LEAVE YOU?

12:05.893 --> 12:06.860
NO, IT WAS --
I MEAN, YOU KNOW, WE TRIED.

12:06.894 --> 12:07.961
WAS SOMEONE CHEATING?

12:07.995 --> 12:08.996
IS SOMEONE
GOING TO LOOK FOR KATE?

12:09.029 --> 12:10.097
[ GASPS ]
WAS IT YOU?

12:10.130 --> 12:11.131
[ GASPS ]
ANSWER THE QUESTION!

12:11.164 --> 12:12.499
OH, JESUS!

12:12.532 --> 12:14.534
BRAIN-HUNGRY ZOMBIES
ARE LESS AGGRESSIVE! BACK OFF!

12:14.567 --> 12:16.236
WE ARE
SO NOT DONE WITH YOU.

12:16.269 --> 12:18.505
WELL, SEEING AS THOUGH ONE OF
YOU CRAWLED DOWN HIS THROAT

12:18.538 --> 12:20.173
AND THE OTHER
CLIMBED UP HIS ASS,

12:20.207 --> 12:22.042
I GUESS THERE'S NO NEED
FOR INTRODUCTIONS.

12:22.075 --> 12:24.945
OKAY, I AM SORRY
ABOUT THE INQUISITION,

12:24.978 --> 12:25.946
BUT I AM HEADING OFF
TO THE LOONY BIN.

12:25.979 --> 12:27.781
UH, YEAH, I KNOW.

12:27.815 --> 12:28.782
AND I WANT TO MAKE SURE
THAT MY BABY'S GONNA BE OKAY.

12:28.816 --> 12:29.950
UH, YEAH, OF COURSE.

12:29.983 --> 12:30.951
I MEAN,
YOU SEEM LIKE A NICE GUY.

12:30.984 --> 12:31.985
HEY,
YOU WANT A BEER?

12:32.019 --> 12:33.086
BUT AS A MOM...
UH...

12:33.120 --> 12:35.088
I'M GONNA GET YOU
A BEER.

12:35.122 --> 12:36.089
...I NEED TO KNOW THAT MY LITTLE
GIRL'S NOT GONNA GET HURT.

12:36.123 --> 12:37.090
OKAY, MOM!

12:37.124 --> 12:38.458
YEAH.

12:38.491 --> 12:40.327
CLEARLY, YOU HAVE FEELINGS
FOR EACH OTHER.

12:40.360 --> 12:41.561
AND I -- I MEAN,
I WOULD NEVER --

12:41.594 --> 12:43.430
BUT IT'S A TRICKY
SITUATION.

12:43.463 --> 12:45.265
THERE'S CHILDREN INVOLVED,
YOU LIVE IN DIFFERENT STATES.

12:45.298 --> 12:46.266
I AGREE.
THAT IS --

12:46.299 --> 12:47.935
LET'S BE HONEST.

12:47.968 --> 12:50.270
I MEAN, THESE LONG-DISTANCE
THINGS, THEY NEVER REALLY --

12:50.303 --> 12:54.274
THE WHOLE THING WOULD BE SOLVED
IF KATE MOVED TO ST. LOUIS.

12:54.307 --> 12:56.343
WHAT -- YOU WANT ME
TO MOVE TO ST. LOUIS?

12:56.376 --> 12:57.344
YEAH.

12:57.377 --> 12:59.079
OH.

12:59.112 --> 13:01.414
I-I MEAN, WE DON'T HAVE TO
MOVE IN TOGETHER,

13:01.448 --> 13:03.083
BUT JUST TO BE CLOSER.

13:03.116 --> 13:04.284
'CAUSE, I MEAN,
THAT WAY...

13:07.020 --> 13:08.889
UM, SO,
THE LOONY BIN, HUH?

13:10.357 --> 13:12.159
[ CHUCKLES SOFTLY ]

13:12.192 --> 13:14.561
YEAH, IT'S SHITTY THAT WE DON'T
LIVE IN THE SAME PLACE,

13:14.594 --> 13:16.063
BUT ST. LOUIS?

13:16.096 --> 13:17.064
IS THAT WHERE WE'RE AT?

13:17.097 --> 13:18.932
I DON'T KNOW.

13:18.966 --> 13:20.467
YOU LOOK VERY HAPPY TOGETHER,
AND HE SEEMS LIKE A NICE GUY.

13:20.500 --> 13:22.202
YOU'RE AN IDIOT

13:22.235 --> 13:24.104
IF YOU THINK I'M DONE
RAKING HIM OVER THE COALS.

13:24.137 --> 13:27.174
I WILL GIVE YOU MY FINAL REPORT
AT THE END OF THE EVENING.

13:27.207 --> 13:28.842
IT'S A DILEMMA.

13:28.876 --> 13:32.279
I MEAN, BY FOLLOWING OUR MEN
ALL OVER THE COUNTRY,

13:32.312 --> 13:36.449
ARE WE, AS WOMEN, JUST FUCKING
FEMINISM RIGHT UP THE BUTT?

13:36.483 --> 13:37.951
AND JUST LIKE THAT,

13:37.985 --> 13:39.419
THE CONVERSATION IS NO LONGER
ABOUT ME.

13:39.452 --> 13:41.254
WELL, I'M SORRY, KATE,
BUT I HAVE A BABY NOW,

13:41.288 --> 13:42.455
SO I'M THINKING FOR TWO.

13:42.489 --> 13:43.957
THREE,
IF YOU INCLUDE MARSHALL.

13:43.991 --> 13:45.492
YOU GETTING COLD FEET
ABOUT THE MOVE?

13:45.525 --> 13:47.060
I DON'T WANT
TO LIVE IN TEXAS.

13:47.094 --> 13:49.963
OH, GOD,
IT'S A HORRIBLE STATE!

13:49.997 --> 13:51.631
THEY ARE ONLY FAMOUS
FOR TWO THINGS --

13:51.664 --> 13:55.235
THEIR STUPID PRESIDENTS
AND THE PEOPLE WHO KILL THEM.

13:55.268 --> 13:57.004
FUCK!

13:57.037 --> 13:58.939
IF NEIL WANTS TO MOVE TO
HOUSTON, HE CAN GO BY HIMSELF.

13:58.972 --> 14:00.908
ALL RIGHT, I KNOW
I'M THE LAST PERSON ON EARTH

14:00.941 --> 14:03.110
WHO HAS THE RIGHT TO COMMENT
ON ANYONE'S BEHAVIOR RIGHT NOW,

14:03.143 --> 14:04.611
BUT I DON'T HAVE
A TON OF TIME LEFT,

14:04.644 --> 14:06.980
SO I'M GONNA DO
WHAT A GOOD SISTER SHOULD.

14:07.014 --> 14:08.415
CAN'T YOU EVER
TAKE MY SIDE?

14:08.448 --> 14:10.083
YOU HAVE SPENT
YOUR ENTIRE LIFE

14:10.117 --> 14:12.619
MAKING ONE MYSTIFYING DECISION
AFTER THE NEXT,

14:12.652 --> 14:15.555
FROM MASSAGE SCHOOL
TO VITA-SELF TO NEIL TO NICK

14:15.588 --> 14:17.958
TO NEIL TO NICK TO NEIL
TO THE BABY?

14:17.991 --> 14:20.227
AND NOW, FOR THE FIRST TIME,
YOU HAVE SOMEONE IN YOUR LIFE

14:20.260 --> 14:21.461
WHO'S DEVOTED TO YOU,
WHO'S TAKEN THE REINS,

14:21.494 --> 14:23.230
I KNOW.

14:23.263 --> 14:25.565
AND WHO WANTS
TO CLEAN UP YOUR LIFE.

14:25.598 --> 14:28.235
SO, YEAH, BECAUSE I LOVE YOU,
I AM TAKING HIS SIDE.

14:28.268 --> 14:30.270
YOU SAID
YOU WERE GONNA GO TO HOUSTON,

14:30.303 --> 14:32.439
SO JUST SHUT YOUR MOUTH,
GROW THE FUCK UP,

14:32.472 --> 14:34.241
AND QUIT ACTING
LIKE AN ASSHOLE.

14:34.274 --> 14:35.342
YA DIG?

14:35.375 --> 14:37.077
DUG.

14:38.111 --> 14:39.179
OH, HEY.

14:39.212 --> 14:41.248
OH, THANKS, SWEETIE.

14:41.281 --> 14:44.017
YOU KNOW, I WAS, UH, I WAS GONNA
TIE UP THE, UH, TURDUCKEN,

14:44.051 --> 14:46.253
IF YOU WANT TO HELP.

14:46.286 --> 14:48.956
OH, WHY DON'T YOU JUST ORDER
DOMINO'S AND BE DONE WITH IT?

14:48.989 --> 14:51.024
I DON'T KNOW
IF YOU'VE SEEN THE COMMERCIALS.

14:51.058 --> 14:52.892
IT TASTES BETTER
LATELY.

14:54.561 --> 14:55.662
[ SIGHS ]

14:55.695 --> 14:57.697
[ SIGHS ]

14:57.730 --> 14:59.366
ISN'T THIS AMAZING?

14:59.399 --> 15:01.301
YEAH, ALMOST AS AMAZING
AS THIS INCREDIBLY CLOSE

15:01.334 --> 15:02.569
FOOTBALL GAME
WE'RE TRYING TO WATCH.

15:02.602 --> 15:03.971
I MEAN,
WHAT A FAMILY.

15:04.004 --> 15:05.038
DO YOU LIKE FOOTBALL,
EVAN?

15:05.072 --> 15:06.039
I'M IN AWE.

15:06.073 --> 15:07.674
I LOVE FOOTBALL.

15:07.707 --> 15:09.542
SUCH COURAGE.

15:09.576 --> 15:11.378
GOD, IF ONLY WE COULD
HEAR THE FUCKING GAME, YOU KNOW?

15:11.411 --> 15:12.445
I ADMIRE YOU, MAX.

15:12.479 --> 15:13.446
NOTHING TO ADMIRE,
BUDDY.

15:13.480 --> 15:15.148
OF COURSE THERE IS.

15:15.182 --> 15:17.217
WITH ALL THE THINGS
THAT ARE GOING ON AROUND HERE,

15:17.250 --> 15:19.219
ALL THE STRESS AND DRAMA?

15:19.252 --> 15:20.954
HEY,
WHAT CAN I TELL YOU?

15:20.988 --> 15:23.023
WELL, YOU GREGSONS
NEVER GIVE IN.

15:23.056 --> 15:26.026
NO MATTER WHAT MESHUGGAAS
LIFE IS THROWING YOUR WAY,

15:26.059 --> 15:27.694
YOU JUST
KEEP ON KEEPIN' ON.

15:27.727 --> 15:31.298
I ALWAYS THINK OF THIS HOUSE
LIKE A GIANT LEMONADE MACHINE.

15:31.331 --> 15:32.365
THE BIGGER THE LEMON --

15:32.399 --> 15:33.967
AAH!

15:34.001 --> 15:35.635
I'M SICK OF HEARING
YOUR FUCKING VOICE!

15:35.668 --> 15:37.570
[ CHOKING ]

15:37.604 --> 15:39.973
...THE BIGGER
THE GLASS OF LEMONADE.

15:40.007 --> 15:41.574
Announcer:
TOUCHDOWN -- NEBRASKA!

15:41.608 --> 15:42.675
OOH! TOUCHDOWN!

15:44.711 --> 15:47.714
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

15:47.747 --> 15:49.316
YOU OKAY?

15:49.349 --> 15:50.317
NOT REALLY.
CAN WE JUST --

15:50.350 --> 15:51.318
HEY, MAX, MAX.

15:51.351 --> 15:52.619
HEY, BUDDY.

15:52.652 --> 15:54.454
HOLD THAT THOUGHT.
HOLD THAT THOUGHT.

15:54.487 --> 15:56.456
TELL KATE THE NAME OF THAT CLUB
IN HOUSTON

15:56.489 --> 15:57.557
THAT BEAVERLAMP PLAYED.

15:57.590 --> 15:58.691
WHAT WAS IT CALLED?

15:58.725 --> 16:00.627
THE IDA LEVENTHAL
YOUTH CENTER.

16:00.660 --> 16:02.762
THAT'S IT.
WE HAD A GREAT TIME.

16:02.795 --> 16:05.098
MARSHALL IS GONNA LOVE
H-TOWN.

16:05.132 --> 16:08.035
WE-WE'VE GOT THE BEACHES,
WE GOT THE RODEO,

16:08.068 --> 16:09.736
WE GOT
THE NASA SPACE CENTER.

16:09.769 --> 16:11.538
OH, WELL, THAT SOUNDS LIKE
OUR MOOSH --

16:11.571 --> 16:14.207
A SUN-SPECKLED,
COW-PUNCHING ASTRONAUT.

16:14.241 --> 16:15.775
EVERY DISPLACED TEEN'S
DREAM.

16:15.808 --> 16:17.377
[ LAUGHTER ]

16:17.410 --> 16:19.712
YOU'RE A GOOD PERSON,
AREN'T YOU?

16:19.746 --> 16:21.481
MM, YEAH.

16:21.514 --> 16:23.716
YOU KNOW, JUST WANT THINGS
TO WORK OUT FOR EVERYBODY,

16:23.750 --> 16:25.418
YOU KNOW?

16:25.452 --> 16:27.420
Evan: HEY, I'M SORRY,
I DIDN'T MEAN TO...

16:27.454 --> 16:28.755
Marshall:
OH, IT'S FINE.

16:28.788 --> 16:30.157
IT'S JUST, YOU KNOW,
KATE TOLD ME, AND...

16:30.190 --> 16:31.658
I KNOW.

16:31.691 --> 16:34.561
BUT I TOTALLY UNDERSTAND.
YOU KNOW, BELIEVE ME.

16:34.594 --> 16:36.563
IT'LL END, THE GRIEF.

16:36.596 --> 16:39.266
UM, YOU KNOW, 'CAUSE, LIKE,
WHEN MY FATHER DIED,

16:39.299 --> 16:40.767
I FELT NOTHING...

16:40.800 --> 16:42.302
WHICH PRETTY MUCH SUMS UP

16:42.335 --> 16:45.272
THE WAY HE FELT ABOUT ME
MY ENTIRE LIFE.

16:45.305 --> 16:48.408
BUT THEN, UH, ABOUT,
I'D SAY LIKE A MONTH LATER,

16:48.441 --> 16:51.378
I REALIZED THERE WAS STILL
ALL THIS, LIKE, UNRESOLVED SHIT

16:51.411 --> 16:53.213
BETWEEN US,
YOU KNOW?

16:53.246 --> 16:55.348
AND IT NEVER GOT BETTER UNTIL
I FIGURED OUT A WAY TO SAY,

16:55.382 --> 16:57.150
YOU KNOW, LIKE ALL THE SHIT
THAT -- THAT I COULDN'T SAY

16:57.184 --> 16:58.585
WHEN HE WAS STILL ALIVE.

16:58.618 --> 17:04.224
I KNOW YOU'RE RIGHT,
BUT FOR WHATEVER REASON...

17:04.257 --> 17:08.228
THERE'S THIS MEMORIAL
WHERE, UM, YOU KNOW...

17:08.261 --> 17:09.629
YEAH.

17:09.662 --> 17:12.465
EVERYBODY'S BEEN THERE,
BUT...I CAN'T.

17:12.499 --> 17:15.502
YOU'LL GO WHEN YOU'RE READY,
YOU KNOW?

17:15.535 --> 17:16.769
THE VERDICT IS IN.

17:16.803 --> 17:18.138
I like him.

17:18.171 --> 17:19.172
[ Singsong voice ]
ME TOO.

17:19.206 --> 17:20.540
TURDUCKEN! TURDUCKEN!

17:20.573 --> 17:23.376
ALMOST AS MUCH FUN TO SAY
AS IT IS TO EAT!

17:23.410 --> 17:24.477
[ CHEERING ]

17:24.511 --> 17:25.778
TUR...DUCK...EN!

17:25.812 --> 17:27.114
Tara: COMING THROUGH!
COMING THROUGH!

17:27.147 --> 17:28.115
YOU WANT TO CARVE IT,
HONEY?

17:28.148 --> 17:29.616
NO, I --

17:29.649 --> 17:30.617
Charmaine: WAIT, MAX,
I WANT TO TAKE A PICTURE.

17:30.650 --> 17:32.152
THIS MEAL IS AMAZING!

17:32.185 --> 17:33.786
Neil: WHO'S GONNA CLEAN UP
ALL THIS SHIT?

17:33.820 --> 17:35.388
I MEAN, THESE TWO ARE
HITTING THE BRICKS TOMORROW.

17:35.422 --> 17:37.090
OH! DID YOU REMEMBER
TO CANCEL THE PAPER?

17:37.124 --> 17:38.491
OH, AND -- AND PUT A STOP
ON THE MAIL?

17:38.525 --> 17:39.792
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
ABOUT SCHOOL?

17:39.826 --> 17:41.428
WELL, YOU'LL BE PLEASED
TO KNOW

17:41.461 --> 17:43.263
THAT EVEN THOUGH
I'LL BE MISSING A FEW WEEKS,

17:43.296 --> 17:46.633
MY GRADES ARE SO GOOD,
THIS GIRL GETS TO GRADUATE!

17:46.666 --> 17:48.268
[ CHEERING ]

17:48.301 --> 17:49.436
HEY, TOAST!
TOAST!

17:49.469 --> 17:50.437
COME ON, TOAST,
TOAST, TOAST!

17:50.470 --> 17:53.506
TOAST, TOAST!

17:53.540 --> 17:55.275
Kate:
THE MAN OF THE HOUR!

17:55.308 --> 17:57.577
WHAT THE FUCK
ARE WE DOING?!

17:57.610 --> 18:00.747
WE'RE HAVING
A GODDAMN PARTY?!

18:00.780 --> 18:02.849
WHILE THE UNIVERSE
IS OUT THERE

18:02.882 --> 18:07.654
DREAMING UP NEW AND DEVIOUS WAYS
TO FUCK US OVER!

18:07.687 --> 18:09.522
LOOK AT THIS FAMILY!

18:09.556 --> 18:14.327
MY BEAUTIFUL WIFE, WHO TRIES
SO HARD TO BE A GOOD PERSON,

18:14.361 --> 18:16.196
GOOD TO OTHER PEOPLE --
AND MY CHILDREN,

18:16.229 --> 18:19.266
WHO'VE NEVER DONE FUCKING
ANYTHING WRONG TO ANYBODY --

18:19.299 --> 18:21.834
NEVER ASKED
TO BE DRAGGED INTO THIS!

18:21.868 --> 18:24.304
GOD,
DID YOU PUT US DOWN HERE

18:24.337 --> 18:28.608
JUST SO YOU COULD TAKE A BIG
FUCKING SHIT ON OUR HEADS?!

18:28.641 --> 18:31.511
WELL, I WANT IT TO STOP!

18:31.544 --> 18:35.515
WHOEVER'S UP THERE LISTENING,
MOVE ON TO SOMEBODY ELSE!

18:35.548 --> 18:37.784
'CAUSE IT'S NOT FUCKING FUNNY!

18:37.817 --> 18:39.586
IT'S NOT FUCKING FAIR!

18:39.619 --> 18:42.355
AND WE DESERVE
SOME FUCKING MERCY!

18:42.389 --> 18:43.756
AAAH!

18:43.790 --> 18:45.792
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

18:50.463 --> 18:52.299
WELL...
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

18:52.332 --> 18:55.435
I CAN'T THINK OF A SINGLE THING
THAT NEEDS TO BE ADDED TO THAT.

18:57.570 --> 18:59.539
ANYONE ELSE?

18:59.572 --> 19:00.607
NO.

19:00.640 --> 19:01.908
NOT A WORD.

19:01.941 --> 19:02.942
WELL PUT.

19:02.975 --> 19:04.811
READY TO EAT?

19:04.844 --> 19:07.914
YEAH. YEAH,
LET'S, UH, LET'S -- LET'S EAT.

19:07.947 --> 19:09.382
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

19:09.416 --> 19:10.650
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

19:17.924 --> 19:21.361
YOU DON'T
HAVE TO DO THAT.

19:21.394 --> 19:23.396
YES, I DO.
[ CHUCKLES ]

19:26.333 --> 19:27.634
I DIDN'T MEAN TO IMPLY

19:27.667 --> 19:31.438
THAT I COULD FIX EVERYTHING
IN ONE WEEKEND

19:31.471 --> 19:34.307
WITH ONE DINNER.

19:34.341 --> 19:38.278
I KNOW IT'S GONNA
TAKE TIME FOR US...

19:38.311 --> 19:40.780
IF EVER.

19:40.813 --> 19:43.516
IT'LL BE
WHAT IT'S SUPPOSED TO BE.

19:49.589 --> 19:52.325
I DON'T THINK I'M GONNA BE ABLE
TO SLEEP TONIGHT.

19:52.359 --> 19:53.726
OH, ME NEITHER.

19:57.297 --> 19:58.798
YOU WANT TO
TAKE A RIDE?

20:10.377 --> 20:11.711
[ ENGINE SHUTS OFF ]

20:13.446 --> 20:15.748
YOU WANT
SOME TIME ALONE?

20:15.782 --> 20:17.216
NO.

20:22.622 --> 20:24.557
[ CAR DOORS CLOSE ]

20:39.506 --> 20:41.941
THERE'S SO MUCH
THAT I NEVER GOT TO SAY.

20:44.977 --> 20:47.514
SO FROM NOW ON,
I'M NOT HOLDING BACK.

20:47.547 --> 20:50.717
IF I HAVE SOMETHING TO SAY
TO YOU, I'M GONNA SAY IT.

20:50.750 --> 20:52.985
I'M OKAY WITH THAT.

21:05.965 --> 21:08.701
[ ELECTRIC GUITAR
PLAYS BLUES MUSIC ]

21:32.625 --> 21:34.561
[ DOGS BARKING ]

21:52.512 --> 21:53.846
[ MUSIC CONTINUES ]

21:53.880 --> 21:56.783
[ DOGS BARKING ]

21:56.816 --> 21:59.586
OH, WHAT IS HE DOING?

21:59.619 --> 22:02.054
[ SIGHS ]
HE'S HAD A TOUGH GO OF IT.

22:02.088 --> 22:03.456
[ CHUCKLES ]

22:03.490 --> 22:05.658
HE CAN DO
WHATEVER HE WANTS.

22:09.729 --> 22:11.864
NEIL?

22:11.898 --> 22:13.032
YEAH?

22:14.601 --> 22:16.403
WILL YOU MARRY ME?

22:16.436 --> 22:17.737
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

22:21.474 --> 22:22.742
NO.

22:23.810 --> 22:25.545
SEE HOW THAT FEELS?

22:25.578 --> 22:27.647
SUCKS, DOESN'T IT?
HUH?

22:27.680 --> 22:30.583
YEAH, I'LL MARRY YOU.

22:30.617 --> 22:31.718
YOU WILL? [ LAUGHS ]

22:31.751 --> 22:32.885
YES, I WILL.

22:32.919 --> 22:34.854
[ MUSIC, BARKING CONTINUES ]

22:38.625 --> 22:40.493
SO,
LET'S TALK ST. LOUIS.

22:40.527 --> 22:43.530
I THINK THAT I KNOW
WHAT I WANT TO DO.

22:43.563 --> 22:46.032
YEAH, OKAY.

22:46.065 --> 22:47.667
OKAY.

22:52.138 --> 22:55.875
I WANT TO SPEND AS MUCH TIME
WITH YOU AS I POSSIBLY CAN.

22:55.908 --> 22:56.876
[ CHUCKLES ]

22:56.909 --> 22:59.446
THIS IS ALL I WANT.

22:59.479 --> 23:04.183
BUT RIGHT NOW, I THINK
THAT I NEED TO MOVE BACK HOME

23:04.216 --> 23:07.086
TO LOOK AFTER MY BROTHER.

23:07.119 --> 23:09.989
I JUST THINK
THAT IT'S THE RIGHT THING TO DO.

23:15.828 --> 23:17.129
I LOVE YOU.

23:20.967 --> 23:22.535
[ CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY ]

23:23.803 --> 23:25.672
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

23:25.705 --> 23:28.608
[ MUSIC CONTINUES ]

23:28.641 --> 23:30.677
HEY! GREGSON!

23:30.710 --> 23:33.713
IT'S ALMOST MIDNIGHT!
JUST SHUT THE HELL UP, WOULD YA?

23:33.746 --> 23:35.915
YOU SHUT THE FUCK UP,
McBURDITT!

23:35.948 --> 23:38.585
I DON'T REMEMBER
ANYONE APPOINTING YOU

23:38.618 --> 23:40.520
KING OF
THIS NEIGHBORHOOD,

23:40.553 --> 23:43.923
YOU MOTHERFUCKING PIECE
OF BIBLE-THUMPING SHIT!

23:43.956 --> 23:46.926
EAT MY SWEATY BALLS,
ASSHOLE!

23:50.963 --> 23:54.667
PLEASE...CONTINUE.

23:54.701 --> 23:56.636
[ MUSIC RESUMES ]

24:01.140 --> 24:03.075
[ MUSIC CONTINUES ]

24:12.852 --> 24:14.787
[ MUSIC STOPS ]

24:33.673 --> 24:35.508
[ WHEELS FUSSES ]

24:35.542 --> 24:36.809
YOU LET ME KNOW
HOW IT GOES.

24:36.843 --> 24:38.044
I WANT
TO HEAR EVERYTHING.

24:38.077 --> 24:39.812
SORRY YOU'RE
MISSING IT.

24:39.846 --> 24:42.248
THERE'S NOTHING MORE ROMANTIC
THAN MUNICIPAL NUPTIALS.

24:42.281 --> 24:43.850
[ LAUGHS ]

24:43.883 --> 24:46.819
I'LL SEND YOU PICTURES
OF THE NEW PLACE.

24:46.853 --> 24:50.122
I CAN'T BELIEVE
I'M DOING THIS WITHOUT YOU.

24:50.156 --> 24:52.659
I DON'T KNOW HOW
YOU DID ANYTHING WITH ME.

24:52.692 --> 24:54.026
[ LAUGHS ]

24:54.060 --> 24:55.161
I LOVE YOU.

24:55.194 --> 24:56.796
I LOVE YOU.
[ SNIFFLES ]

24:56.829 --> 24:58.598
[ SMOOCHES ]

24:58.631 --> 25:00.066
KATE, WATER 15th,
POWER 20th.

25:00.099 --> 25:01.801
I KNOW. I GOT IT.
[ SIGHS ]

25:03.169 --> 25:04.904
Keep an eye
on your brother.

25:04.937 --> 25:07.707
[ SIGHS ] I WILL.

25:14.080 --> 25:15.815
WHEN YOU GET TO BOSTON,

25:15.848 --> 25:18.184
DON'T LET 'EM PULL OUT
ALL THE GOOD PARTS.

25:19.686 --> 25:21.253
[ SIGHS ]

25:23.823 --> 25:25.892
[ SNIFFLES ]

25:28.027 --> 25:29.696
YOU GUYS
ARE MY GOOD PARTS.

25:29.729 --> 25:31.263
[ SIGHS ]

25:31.297 --> 25:33.566
HEY,
WE BETTER GET GOING.

25:33.600 --> 25:35.334
YEAH, IT'S TIME
TO BOUNCE AROUND IN MY HEAD

25:35.367 --> 25:37.069
[ Laughing ] UNTIL I LAND
IN THE BANANA FACTORY.

25:37.103 --> 25:38.705
[ SOBS ]

25:38.738 --> 25:40.673
[ SUPERTRAMP'S
"THE LOGICAL SONG" PLAYS ]

25:44.777 --> 25:49.716
* WHEN I WAS YOUNG, IT SEEMED
THAT LIFE WAS SO WONDERFUL *

25:49.749 --> 25:51.584
* A MIRACLE

25:51.618 --> 25:53.653
* OH, IT WAS BEAUTIFUL,
MAGICAL *

25:53.686 --> 25:54.654
* AND ALL THE BIRDS
IN THE TREES *

25:54.687 --> 25:56.188
GOT EVERYTHING?

25:56.222 --> 25:58.090
* THEY'D BE SINGING
SO HAPPILY *

25:58.124 --> 26:01.761
* OH, JOYFULLY

26:01.794 --> 26:06.966
* OH, PLAYFULLY WATCHING ME

26:06.999 --> 26:12.304
* BUT THEN THEY SENT ME AWAY
TO TEACH ME HOW TO BE SENSIBLE *

26:12.338 --> 26:14.240
* LOGICAL

26:14.273 --> 26:15.875
* OH, RESPONSIBLE, PRACTICAL

26:15.908 --> 26:18.277
I WENT AHEAD AND SET
THE CHILD LOCKS ON YOUR DOOR,

26:18.310 --> 26:21.180
SO YOU'RE GONNA NEED ME
IF YOU WANT TO GET OUT.

26:21.213 --> 26:23.382
[ CHUCKLES ]
PROBABLY A GOOD IDEA.

26:23.415 --> 26:29.288
* OH, INTELLECTUAL, CYNICAL

26:29.321 --> 26:35.762
* THERE ARE TIMES
WHEN ALL THE WORLD'S ASLEEP *

26:35.795 --> 26:38.698
* THE QUESTIONS RUN TOO DEEP

26:38.731 --> 26:39.999
[ WINDOW WHIRRING ]

26:40.032 --> 26:45.705
* FOR SUCH A SIMPLE MA-A-A-A-N

26:45.738 --> 26:47.774
* WON'T YOU PLEASE

26:47.807 --> 26:51.878
* PLEASE TELL ME
WHAT WE'VE LEARNED *

26:51.911 --> 26:55.715
* I KNOW IT SOUNDS ABSURD

26:55.748 --> 27:01.654
* BUT PLEASE TELL ME
WHO I A-A-A-AM *

27:01.688 --> 27:05.291
* WHO I A-A-A-AM

27:05.324 --> 27:09.295
* WHO I A-A-A-A-AM

27:09.328 --> 27:13.666
* WHO I A-A-A-A-A-M

27:13.700 --> 27:14.901
YEAH!

27:17.469 --> 27:18.871
WHOO!

27:21.107 --> 27:23.009
HEY!

27:29.816 --> 27:33.119
'CAUSE I WAS FEELING
SO LOGICAL.

27:38.024 --> 27:40.960
D-D-D-D-DIGITAL.

27:40.993 --> 27:43.262
YEAH, ONE, TWO, THREE.
